caption: Lovely little garden in the middle of the city chaos. We always managed to find seating but it seems to be busy most times due to its small size. It is extremely clean and pleasant with beautiful planting, birds and the fountain sounds. I found it very relaxing and one of my favourite spots in Paris. We had some baguettes here and relaxed after walking for awhile whilst on holiday. It seems to be popular with locals also.
Beautiful square, great place to rest and spend some time with some fancy pigeons. in Aug/Sept the flowers are really lovely.

It's an enchanting little park with playground. Our girls loved it and we were comfortable having them play. There's a fence around for added safety and lots of greeneryaking it feel more tranquil. Only issue worth raising is the toilet, it's old, broken and not very sanitary, but as this review is about the park, 5 stars!
